odel with increased atmospheric CO2 concentrations (1996) Nature, 382, pp. 56-60; Latif, M., Keenlyside, N.S., El Niño/southern oscillation response to global warming (2008) PNAS, , DOI:10.1073/pnas.0710860105; Liu, Z., Vavrus, S., He, F., Wen, N., Zhong, Y., Rethinking tropical ocean response to global warming: the enhanced equatorial warming (2005) Journal of Climate, 18, pp. 4684-4700; Vavrus, S., Liu, Z., Understanding the response of the tropical atmosphere-ocean system to increased CO2 using equilibrium asynchronous coupling (2002) Climate Dynamics, 19, pp. 355-369; Vecchi, G.A., Soden, B.J., Wittenberg, A.T., Held, I.M., Leetmaa, A., Harrison, M.J., Weakening of tropical Pacific atmospheric circulation due to anthropogenic forcing (2006) Nature, 441, pp. 73-76; Vecchi, G.A., Harrison, D.E., On the termination of the 2002-2003 El Niño event (2003) Geophysics Research Letters, 30, p. 1964. , DOI:10.1029/2003GL017564; Vecchi, G.A., The termination of the 1997-1998 El Niño. Part II: mechanisms of atmospheric change (2006) Journal of Climate, 19, pp. 2647-2664; Yu, B., Boer, G.J., The roles of radiation and dynamic processes in the El Niño-like response to global warming (2002) Climate Dynamics, 19, pp. 539-553","Kug, J.-S.; Korea Ocean Research and Development Institute AnsanSouth Korea; email: jskug@kordi.re.kr",,,,,,,,08998418,,IJCLE,,"English","Int. J. Climatol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-79955035968
